WGET:
            wget stands for "web get". It is a command-line utility which downloads files over a network.


The command will download single file and stores in a current directory. It also shows download progress, size, date and time while downloading.
Command
wget http://www.openss7.org/repos/tarballs/strx25-0.9.2.1.tar.bz2


Using -O (uppercase) option, downloads file with different file name. Here we have given wget.zip file name as show below.
Command:
wget -O wget.zip http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/wget/wget-1.5.3.tar.gz



Restart a download which got stopped in the middle using wget -c option as shown below.
Command:
Wget -c http://www.openss7.org/repos/tarballs/strx25-0.9.2.1.tar.bz2


Command:
wget -b http://www.openss7.org/repos/tarballs/strx25-0.9.2.1.tar.bz2



Emulating a Complete Website


		If you wish to retain a copy of any website that you may like to refer to/read locally, or maybe save a copy of your blog to the hard disk as back up, you may execute the wget command with mirror option, as follows:
Command:
			wget --mirror [Website Name]


Download Multiple Files / URLs Using Wget -i


		First, store all the download files or URLs in a text file 
Command:
wget -i download-file-list.txt
